# Inverted Pendulum on a Cart - Simulink & MATLAB

This project simulates an inverted pendulum mounted on a cart using a nonlinear dynamic model in Simulink. The system is stabilized using a PID controller.

## 📦 Contents

- `Simulink/model.slx` — nonlinear model of the inverted pendulum
- `MATLAB/` — dynamics and filter implementations
- `figures/` — simulation results

## 🎯 Goals

- Simulate inverted pendulum dynamics
- Apply PID to stabilize upright position

## 🚀 Run

1. Open `Simulink/model.slx`
2. Run the simulation
3. (Optional) Tune PID gains

## 🛠️ Requirements

- MATLAB R202x4
- Simulink
- Control System Toolbox (if PID block is used)

---

Feel free to fork or build on this for control system or robotics projects!
